&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;One theory we have is this could be due to the lock handles being uninitialized since the initialization was removed as part of &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/40764&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/40764&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Seems like the ldlm lock at 0xffff000401b59ca0 shows a pattern of self-referential pointers, which could mean the handles array could be pointing to uninitialized garbage. However, we saw this repeatedly occur for multiple hours, likely from Lustre recovery replaying the locks. We were only able to stop the crashes by eventually aborting recovery/hitting hard recovery timeout.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
